##
## dispatcher.list — FreeSWITCH instance pool for Kamailio dispatcher module
##
## Format:
##   setid  destination_uri            flags  priority  attrs
##
## setid    : Pool ID — must match ds_select_dst(1, ...) in kamailio.cfg
## dest_uri : SIP URI of the FreeSWITCH instance
##            Uses Docker service hostname (resolved by Docker embedded DNS)
## flags    : 0 = active (monitored); 2 = inactive (skip but keep in list)
## priority : 0 = equal (round-robin ignores this; use for weighted if alg changes)
## attrs    : Key=value metadata (informational only; used in xlog/debug)
##
## Port assignment:
##   fs1 listens on SIP port 5070 (Kamailio owns 5060)
##   fs2 listens on SIP port 5070 (each container has its own port internally)
##   Host-level mapping: fs1 -> host:5070, fs2 -> host:5071
##   Inside Docker network: each container exposes :5070 on its own IP
##
## To add a third instance:
##   1  sip:fs3:5070  0  0  duid=fs3
##
## To temporarily disable an instance (e.g., for maintenance):
##   2  sip:fs1:5070  2  0  duid=fs1
##   (flag=2 marks it inactive; Kamailio will not route to it)
##
## Apply changes at runtime (no restart needed):
##   docker exec kamailio kamctl dispatcher reload
##

# Set 1: FreeSWITCH media server pool
# All instances are identical in role — dispatcher uses round-robin (alg=4)

1  sip:fs1:5070  0  0  duid=fs1;role=media
1  sip:fs2:5070  0  0  duid=fs2;role=media
